You can make use of the [**`|truncatechars`** template filter [Django-doc]](https://docs.djangoproject.com/en/dev/ref/templates/builtins/#truncatechars):

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;td&amp;gt;{{ row.name&lt;b&gt;|truncatechars:9&lt;/b&gt; }}&amp;lt;/td&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;

This will thus limit the number of characters to nine (in this case). If the name is shorter than or has exactly nine characters, then it will render the name. Otherwise it will render the first characters, followed by an ellipsis (&amp;hellip;).

You can make use of [*Bootstrap&#39;s tooltips](https://getbootstrap.com/docs/4.3/components/tooltips/) and add a tooltip like:

&lt;pre&gt;&lt;code&gt;&amp;lt;td&amp;gt;
    &amp;lt;span &lt;b&gt;data-toggle=&amp;quot;tooltip&amp;quot; title=&amp;quot;{{ row.name }}&amp;quot;&lt;/b&gt;&amp;gt;
    {{ row.name|truncatechars:9 }}
    &amp;lt;/span&amp;gt;
